            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1"> 		
                    Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-4">
                    <unclear>9</unclear>th year of the glorious king Kulottuṅga Cōḻa, emperor of the three worlds.
                </p>
                
                <p n="4-9">
                    Among the <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign>s<note>Literally: slaves of god.</note> of the Lord Nalla Nāyaṉār
                    ...
                </p>
                <p n="9-12">
                    In the temple of this Lord,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">singing</supplied> the first decade of the Tiruvempāvai <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruvapavai</foreign></supplied>,
                    proceeding ahead during the hunt festival,
                    climbing the glorious car,
                    these <supplied reason="subaudible">prerogatives</supplied>
                    ...
                </p>
                <p>
                    Having deposited in payment half a <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign> of gold in the glorious treasure as the price <supplied reason="subaudible">fixed</supplied> by Taṇṭēcurar,<note>Sanskrit Caṇḍeśvara.</note>
                    we have given <supplied reason="subaudible">these prerogatives</supplied> to these, we, the <foreign>tāṉattār</foreign>s<note>Temple officers.</note> in this temple.
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
